        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 5:54AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 554 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arcola, or 10 miles south of Greensboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Greensboro, Newbern, Judson College, Morgan Springs,
Cedarville, Laneville, and Folsom.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
